description:
The Philippines just received a new fleet of advanced ships from Japan  a major step in boosting its maritime power and protecting its waters in the South China Sea. These modern vessels will help the Philippine Coast Guard patrol its territory, enhance sea surveillance, and strengthen national defense.

But Japan isnt the only ally stepping up. The United States and France have also deepened cooperation with the Philippines through joint exercises, defense training, and naval partnerships. Together, these alliances are helping the country build a stronger and more capable maritime presence.
